Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine light red-brown; cream slip. Ovoid stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Theulytos. Trimmed. Same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX DI 1461.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0501)
